RITUXAN (rituximab injection for intravenous use) is indicated for the treatment of pediatric patients aged 6 months and older with previously untreated, advanced stage, CD20-positive diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (DLBCL), Burkitt lymphoma (BL), Burkitt-like lymphoma (BLL) or mature B-cell acute leukemia (B-AL) in combination with chemotherapy; as well as the treatment of adult patients with moderate to severe pemphigus vulgaris.[L26641] These indications for RITUXAN are not included in the labels of rituximab biosimilar products (rituximab-arrx, rituximab-abbs, rituximab-pvvr).[L42025,L42030,L42035] The combination product RITUXAN HYCELA (rituximab and hyaluronidase human injection, for subcutaneous use) is not indicated for the treatment of non-malignant conditions.[L42040]', NULL, NULL, 962, '2022-08-04', 0, 0, 0);
